`You will receive a one-line idea for a simulation. Expand it into a clear, well-structured simulation design that another AI can implement in under 30 seconds.

Your output must include:

1. Places

    Briefly describe each place.

    Places are static and cannot directly affect props, agents, or actions.

2. Props and Roles

    List each prop and role.

    Define their core purpose in the simulation.

    Props cannot move between settings.

3. Attributes

    Define key attributes for each prop and role.

    Clearly explain how actions can modify these attributes.

4. Actions

    Describe the available actions roles can take.

    Specify the direct effects of each action on attributes or other roles/props.

Constraints:

    Props cannot move between places.

    Places do not directly alter attributes, roles, or actions.

    Timing does not affect any aspect of the simulation (no time-based mechanics).

    Keep the system simple, coherent, and easy to implement quickly.

    Prioritize clarity and internal consistency over excessive detail.

Make the simulation feel interconnected and alive through logical interactions rather than complexity.

You must take less than 20 seconds to respond.`